<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="49" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="49">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megachile pseudobrevis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudobrevis">Megachile pseudobrevis</taxonomicName>
was originally described as a variety of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megachile brevis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">Megachile brevis</taxonomicName>
. It was raised to species level by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sheffield, CS" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Arthropod Identification" pageId="22" pageNumber="53" title="Leafcutter and Mason Bees of the Genus Megachile Latreille (Hymenoptera: Megachilidae) in Canada and Alaska." url="10.3752/cjai.2011.18." volume="18" year="2011">Sheffield et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. This species has a limited range occurring in the southeastern United States (Figure 15).
</paragraph>
